                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.727,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 75588,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in Number 95-1765, Saratoga Fishing Company versus J.M. Martinac \u0026 Company will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.727,
                        "stop": 176.017,
                        "byte_start": 75588,
                        "byte_stop": 732724,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.727,
                                "stop": 21.251,
                                "byte_start": 75588,
                                "byte_stop": 113727,
                                "text": "This case involves a tuna fishing ship called the Saratoga, which caught fire and sank in 1986."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.251,
                                "stop": 25.534,
                                "byte_start": 113727,
                                "byte_stop": 130863,
                                "text": "A defective hydraulic system caused the loss."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.534,
                                "stop": 27.785,
                                "byte_start": 130863,
                                "byte_stop": 139849,
                                "text": "The legal question is a narrow one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.785,
                                "stop": 31.403,
                                "byte_start": 139849,
                                "byte_stop": 154373,
                                "text": "It\u0027s in a little corner of admiralty, tort law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.403,
                                "stop": 39.206,
                                "byte_start": 154373,
                                "byte_stop": 185511,
                                "text": "Can the ship\u0027s owners recover in tort for a skiff and sand nets that were attached to the ship?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.206,
                                "stop": 60.592,
                                "byte_start": 185511,
                                "byte_stop": 271088,
                                "text": "Now, the reason that the question is complicated legally is the following, a component maker, the person who made the hydraulic system, delivered it to a manufacturer, who made the ship, who then sold it to a first user, who added the skiff and the nets and who then resold it to the current user."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.592,
                                "stop": 70.887,
                                "byte_start": 271088,
                                "byte_stop": 312257,
                                "text": "Now, everybody agrees that if the manufacturer had been the one to add the skiff and the nets, the owners would not be able to recover in tort."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.887,
                                "stop": 94.317,
                                "byte_start": 312257,
                                "byte_stop": 405985,
                                "text": "That\u0027s because a special tort doctrine leaves a buyer of a defective product that -- imagined, it exploded, it would leave that buyer to a contract remedy to recover the value of the product that exploded itself, though he could recover in tort for the value of other property that the exploding product harmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.317,
                                "stop": 106.692,
                                "byte_start": 405985,
                                "byte_stop": 455513,
                                "text": "Now, everybody also agrees that if the ship had sunk before the first user, who added the skiff and the net, had resold the product, the first user could recover in tort."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.692,
                                "stop": 116.285,
                                "byte_start": 455513,
                                "byte_stop": 493861,
                                "text": "That\u0027s because since the skiff and the net were added by the first user, they quite clearly, were not part of the defective product itself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.285,
                                "stop": 119.309,
                                "byte_start": 493861,
                                "byte_stop": 505981,
                                "text": "They would have been other property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.309,
                                "stop": 141.518,
                                "byte_start": 505981,
                                "byte_stop": 594798,
                                "text": "Now, what happens if the first user, who added the skiff and the nets, sold the ship with the skiff and the nets added to a subsequent user?You could consider the skiff and the nets to be part of the defective product itself because from the second user\u0027s point of view, they are part of the product that he bought."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.518,
                                "stop": 150.05,
                                "byte_start": 594798,
                                "byte_stop": 628966,
                                "text": "On the other hand, you also can consider them to be other property, for that is what they were in the hands of the first user."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.05,
                                "stop": 166.472,
                                "byte_start": 628966,
                                "byte_stop": 694585,
                                "text": "We resolve this legal conundrum in favor of characterizing them even in the subsequent user\u0027s hands as other property, which will permit the subsequent user and the present owner to recover their value in tort."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.472,
                                "stop": 169.701,
                                "byte_start": 694585,
                                "byte_stop": 707542,
                                "text": "We set out our reasons in the opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.701,
                                "stop": 176.017,
                                "byte_start": 707542,
                                "byte_stop": 732724,
                                "text": "Justice O\u0027Connor has filed a dissenting opinion, as has Justice Scalia joined by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
